==English==
===Etymology===
In Latin ''Nekros'' means [[corpse]]
===Noun===
'''necromancy'''
#[[Magic]] involving the [[dead]] or [[death]]

Necromancy is derived from the Greek Necromantia. Necro(the dead) Mancy(witchcraft or magic). Many different cultures have used necromancy. There is therefore much controversy as to how it is used. There are two clear divisions of necromancy however, that branch in which one consults directly with the corpse or spirit, and that branch wherein one takes the spirit within oneself, thereby using its knowledge (usually to glean the future).